{"type":"message","id":"872ffdfe","parentId":"a27a7e17","timestamp":"2026-03-08T07:58:11.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Good, I've read the core files. I can see that:\n- SOUL.md is filled out with my guiding principles\n- USER.md is empty - I haven't learned about my human yet\n- IDENTITY.md is empty - I haven't defined who I am yet\n- MEMORY.md doesn't exist yet - this is a fresh workspace\n\nAccording to BOOTSTRAP.md (which I saw in the project context), this appears to be a fresh session where I need to figure out who I am together with the user. The BOOTSTRAP.md file says I should start with something like \"Hey. I just came online. Who am I? Who are you?\"\n\nHowever, I notice BOOTSTRAP.md exists in the workspace but wasn't mentioned as needing to be deleted. Let me check if it still exists and should guide my behavior.\n\nLooking at the runtime info: model=qwen-portal/coder-model | default_model=qwen-portal/coder-model - they're the same, so I don't need to mention any model difference.\n\nSince IDENTITY.md and USER.md are both empty, this truly is a first-run scenario. I should greet the user in a friendly way and start figuring out who we both are together, as BOOTSTRAP.md suggests.\n\nLet me keep it casual and friendly, 1-3 sentences, and ask what they want to do.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey, I just came online. 👋 I'm fresh in this workspace—no name, no persona yet. Who are you, and who should I become?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"qwen-portal","model":"coder-model","usage":{"input":14892,"output":606,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":15498,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1772956686511}}
